article.description: — John-Michael Wright had 24 points as High Point edged past Charleston Southern 77-73 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Wright lifts High Point past Charleston Southern 77-73
article.linkText: Wright lifts High Point past Charleston Southern 77-73
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- — John-Michael Wright had 24 points as High Point edged past Charleston Southern 77-73 on Thursday night. Bryant Randleman had 16 points for High Point (8-10, 6-7 Big South Conference). Lydell Elmore added 14 points and nine rebounds, and Alex Holt had 10 points. High Point totaled 55 second-half points, a season high. Phlandrous Fleming Jr. had 26 points, 11 rebounds and four blocks for the Buccaneers (1-16, 0-13), whose losing streak stretched to 13 games. Melvin Edwards Jr. added 10 points and Sean Price had eight rebounds and six assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
